    (commutator with T^1, T^2 nonzero), confirming sub-block operators
    are not iso-singlet scalars.

  - Block 10: generation-indexed decomposition gives Z^2 = 6
    uniformly across three generations -- no hierarchy.

  - Block 11-12: uniform y_s/g_s = 1/sqrt(6) for all six species;
    mass predictions empirically falsified across all six species.

  - Block 13: exact SU(2)_L forbids (1,1)-(3,1) operator mixing at
    M_Pl at any loop order.

  Outcome C: flavor-column decomposition of H_unit is NOT framework-
  native. The retention gap identified in the b-quark note must be
  closed by a primitive in candidate classes #2, #3, or #4.

